[SN]TITLE[SN]
Michel Platini wants Fifa World Cup report to be made public

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Uefa president Michel Platini wants football's world governing body Fifa to publish the full report into alleged World Cup bidding corruption.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fifa president Sepp Blatter previously rejected calls to publish the complete findings of American lawyer Michael Garcia, who conducted the inquiry.
But Platini thinks there needs to be greater transparency.
"I have no issue with the findings and recommendations being made available to the public," he said.
